        "username": "Martin_Zwick",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/9fc29f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-03-28T06:17:45.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>2018 Pierre-Yves Colin-Morey Meursault</strong><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<em>Attacke!</em></p>\n<p>What a contrast in style to the previous Chablis by Dauvissat which was all about balance&amp;harmony and elegance.This Meursault attacks your palate, but in a good way.  Full of energy, grip, acidity, freshness and explosions on your palate. I would recommend to serve it at the end of a tasting during a long night. After the first sip you feel immediately fully awake, haha.</p>\n<p>BTW, it\u2019s the entry level Meursault from the estate and it is such mind-blowing.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\nP.S.  it looks like that the wine settles down on Day 2 based on reviews at cellartracker. Anyway I loved this wild style.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/1/d/1db77a550cbab2ddb92d46ca590c9c5253afc819.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG_9368.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"4eSWEZ0fFPYg8Xbag4WYXU7nO3v\" width=\"2861\" height=\"4024\"></p>",
